1009
00:51:25,375 --> 00:51:27,515
- The odds are against her.
- Yes, I can see it.

1010
00:51:27,875 --> 00:51:29,274
But she's not letting it go.

1011
00:51:29,275 --> 00:51:30,615
- She doesn't give up.
- She doesn't give up.

1012
00:51:31,085 --> 00:51:33,554
If she plays well, she could go overtime.

1013
00:51:33,555 --> 00:51:34,714
- That's right.
- Overtime.

1014
00:51:34,715 --> 00:51:36,154
So she still has a chance.

1015
00:51:36,155 --> 00:51:38,354
- Her opponent shot a three-pointer, - Yes.

1016
00:51:38,355 --> 00:51:39,725
but she won't give up.

1017
00:51:44,695 --> 00:51:46,495
This is the fifth day's morning.

1018
00:51:52,065 --> 00:51:53,734
- What is it?
- What? They're back in the lodging.

1019
00:51:53,735 --> 00:51:55,475
- They're back in the lodging.
- That's the lodging.

1020
00:51:55,775 --> 00:51:57,045
They didn't sleep out.

1021
00:51:58,975 --> 00:52:01,015
- Thanks for the food.
- Thanks for the food.

1022
00:52:03,015 --> 00:52:04,115
It's delicious.

1023
00:52:05,615 --> 00:52:08,055
- Did you...
- Go to a supermarket?

1024
00:52:08,615 --> 00:52:11,885
No. Yeong Gi's mom harvested potato sweet from her garden.

1025
00:52:13,795 --> 00:52:16,055
It's sweet potato, not potato sweet, Mother.

1026
00:52:16,295 --> 00:52:18,624
It's sweet potato, not potato sweet, Mother.

1027
00:52:18,625 --> 00:52:19,835
You sound the same!

1028
00:52:20,395 --> 00:52:21,635
How many times did you imitate it?

1029
00:52:22,735 --> 00:52:23,835
It's sweet potato, not potato sweet, Mother.

1030
00:52:25,305 --> 00:52:26,504
Things aren't easy from the morning.

1031
00:52:26,505 --> 00:52:27,835
It's sweet potato, not potato sweet, Mother.

1032
00:52:31,775 --> 00:52:34,944
(The doorbell suddenly rings.)

1033
00:52:34,945 --> 00:52:36,374
- What?
- What is it?

1034
00:52:36,375 --> 00:52:37,445
